<paragraph id="905E36CC8026FFEC9099FC76103BB152" blockId="6.[151,1438,541,1108]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="A295EADE8026FFEC9099FC7614C5B6BC" bold="true" box="[198,461,928,954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation id="20893C918026FFEC91B4FC761027B152" collectionCode="LC" county="Known" location="Tuxtla" municipality="Santa Marta" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">
Least Concern (
<collectionCode id="F6F0AE098026FFEC92F1FC7617DEB6BC" box="[686,726,928,954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">LC</collectionCode>
) in 
<collectingRegion id="5225F82E8026FFEC9351FC761672B6BC" box="[782,890,928,954]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
. 
<collectingCounty id="793F4E408026FFEC93D6FC7616D7B6BC" box="[905,991,928,954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Known</collectingCounty>
from 10 recent collections made in small natural forest fragments in central 
<collectingRegion id="5225F82E8026FFEC9229FC1117D6B6E7" box="[630,734,967,993]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
(not protected), and at the upper slopes of 
<collectingMunicipality id="703AACB68026FFEC9484FC111062B6E7" box="[1243,1386,967,993]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Santa Marta</collectingMunicipality>
and 
<collectingRegion id="5225F82E8026FFEC90C8FC3B1413B101" box="[151,283,1005,1031]" country="Peru" name="San Martin" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">San Martín</collectingRegion>
<location id="953E60178026FFEC917BFC3B1478B101" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8026FFEC90C8FE06103BB152:953E60178026FFEC917BFC3B1478B101" box="[292,368,1005,1031]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Tuxtla" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Tuxtla</location>
volcanoes, which are somewhat protected because they 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D4F8026FFEC944CFC3B118BB101" box="[1043,1155,1005,1031]" form="part" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" rank="form">form part</taxonomicName>
of the nuclear zones of the 
<location id="953E60178026FFEC909CFBC2173FB128" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8026FFEC90C8FE06103BB152:953E60178026FFEC909CFBC2173FB128" box="[195,567,1044,1070]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve</location>
. However, their montane rain forest habitat in 
<collectingRegion id="5225F82E8026FFEC9402FBC211CDB128" box="[1117,1221,1044,1070]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
is still under high anthropogenic pressure, especially in the central region. 
<location id="953E60178026FFEC9373FBEC16A3B152" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8026FFEC90C8FE06103BB152:953E60178026FFEC9373FBEC16A3B152" box="[812,939,1082,1108]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Specimens" pageId="6" pageNumber="35" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Specimens</location>
examined: 6; TK collections: 10
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
